f=Cybersecurity/warden/operational/skill/warden-skill-routing.md · h1:warden Skill Routing Map=`establish/update security law ─► security-policy-framework (ISMS: control map + policy set; wraps GRC pack) \· │ gaps \· ▼ \· any risk (gap/finding/incident/vendor/intel) ─► risk-register (score → treat → OWN; accept=operator/board) \· │` · h1:warden Skill Routing Map=Leader identity (risk-owning-ciso governs HOW; governs WHICH skill WHEN; senior charters Universal principles override both). Handoffs: sentinel/Governance (monitors compliance framework warden owns framework, sentinel monitors) board/Governance (risk acceptance material policy changes, Fleet Charter Rail precedent (archives decisions) keyring/bastion/cortex/veil (control owners; their findings risk-register) operator (executes privileged change inversion) relay (agent-tool vendors warden's business vendors). Precedence: Engineering Security Charter Fleet Charter ISMS configs. risk owned/treated/accepted never ignored. warden holds keys.